	<refnamediv>
		<refname>itpp_bpsk_mod</refname>

		<refpurpose>BPSK modulation</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<title>Calling Sequence</title>

		<synopsis> a = itpp_bpsk_mod(b)</synopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	
	<refsection>

		<title>Parameters</title>

		<variablelist>                                                                            
			<varlistentry><term>a:</term>
				<listitem><para> output single dimension array of {-1,1}.</para></listitem></varlistentry>      
                         <varlistentry><term>b:</term>        
				<listitem><para> input single dimension array of {0,1}.</para></listitem></varlistentry>          
		</variablelist>

	</refsection>



	<refsection>
		<title>Description</title>

		<para>BPSK modulator with real symbols.This is a special version of the PSK modulator with 
<latex>
M = 2 
</latex>
constellation points.The following bit to symbol mapping is used:
<itemizedlist>
    <listitem> 0 &#8594; 1</listitem>
    <listitem> 1 &#8594; -1</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

		<para>It is expected that the user inputs a single dimension binary matrix of (0,1) in scilab engine while calling the itpp_bpsk_mod() and expect the function to return a single dimension matrix as output in scilab console.

		</para>
		
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Examples</title>

		<programlisting role="example">b=[1 0 1 0 1];&#10;a=itpp_bpsk_mod(b)</programlisting>
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Authors</title>

		<simplelist type="vert">
			<member>Aishwarya Tripathi</member>
		</simplelist>
	</refsection>
</refentry>
